pull_request.title: Include .dylib instructions for MacOS.
pull_request.body:
Resolves #23  by including an example of setting MacOS Environment Variable with liboqs.dylib.

- I removed reference to the specific platform instructions, because it was ambiguous about whether that referred to the current repo or the liboqs repo.
- I notice an opportunity to include links to sponsor organizations et al. I kept this focussed on issue-23 for future tracking, but more than happy to go through it, since I already have a fork cloned etc.

pull_request.title: generic optimized build type added
pull_request.body: The proposed build type "Generic" generates a variant that can run on Intel CPUs regardless of feature set _and_ is O3 compiled. For the time being, arguably the best docker-build target for execution on all x86_64s (incl. CPU-heterogeneous CI environments): When doing TLS-handshake perf tests (openssl s_time), often, AVX2-enabled code executed _slower_ than non-optimised code... Did you encounter this too? Possibly relevant reference: https://blog.cloudflare.com/on-the-dangers-of-intels-frequency-scaling/
